relationships.name: hasPostdirectionalSymbol
relationships.description: specifies a geographic directional symbol that follows the street name and street suffix in a street address

relationships.name: hasPredirectionalSymbol
relationships.description: specifies a geographic directional symbol that occurs after the primary street number but before the street name in a street address

relationships.name: hasPreferredSettlementCurrency
relationships.description: indicates the preferred currency for settlement purposes

description._: indicates a premium payable for a contract based on the index

relationships.name: hasPremiumAmount
relationships.description: indicates the premium paid to a bond holder when the bond is called

relationships.name: hasPrimaryAccountHolder
relationships.description: relates an account to a client or customer that is considered the primary owner of the account

relationships.name: hasPrimaryAccountNumber
relationships.description: specifies the account number displayed on the face of the card

relationships.name: hasPrimaryAddressNumber
relationships.description: specifies a a location with respect to a given street

relationships.name: hasPrimaryResidence
relationships.description: identifies a dwelling where an individual resides the majority of the year

relationships.name: hasPrincipalManagingParty
relationships.description: indicates a controlling party that is responsible for the management of daily business operations

relationships.name: hasPrincipalParty
relationships.description: identifies the main or principal party to a contract

relationships.name: hasPriorityLevel
relationships.description: relates a guaranty to some relative ranking that the guaranty has in the context of the contract, for example for a credit enhancement priority

relationships.name: hasPublisher
relationships.description: indicates the party in the role of issuing the information

relationships.name: hasPutFrequency
relationships.description: indicates the recurring window of time in which the put feature can be exercised

relationships.name: hasQuotationBlockAmountBasis
relationships.description: indicates the amount of the dealt currency which would be exchanged in a trade for which the stated spot rate applies

description._: indicates the nature of the pricing quotations to be requested from banks and/or dealers when determining the market value of the reference obligation for purposes of cash settlement

relationships.name: hasRatingScore
relationships.description: indicates the grade or score associated with a rating with respect to a particular rating scale

relationships.name: hasRedemptionAmount
relationships.description: indicates the amount of the principal paid with a redemption payment

relationships.name: hasRedemptionPremium
relationships.description: indicates the premium price per share over the market price, if any, that must be paid in order to redeem the stock

relationships.name: hasRemarketingAgent
relationships.description: identifies the dealer responsible for reselling to investors securities (such as variable rate demand obligations and other tender option bonds) that have been tendered for purchase by their owner.

relationships.name: hasResidence
relationships.description: identifies a dwelling where an individual lives

relationships.name: hasResponsibleParty
relationships.description: identifies a party that has some assignment, commitment or obligation with respect to the formal organization

relationships.name: hasReturnLeg
relationships.description: indicates the leg of a return swap whose payments are based on the return of an underlying asset

relationships.name: hasSecondaryAccountHolder
relationships.description: relates an account to a client or customer that is considered a secondary, co-owner of the account

relationships.name: hasSecondaryUnit
relationships.description: specifies an individual unit within a larger structure, such as an apartment, office, hangar, slip, mailbox, and so forth, at a given street address

relationships.name: hasSettlementAmount
relationships.description: indicates the monetary amount required for cash settlement

relationships.name: hasSettlementTerms
relationships.description: relates a derivative to contractual terms specific to the settlement process

description._: indicates the payment status for shares issued

relationships.name: hasStartingBalance
relationships.description: relates an account statement to the amount of money available in that account at the beginning of the statement period

relationships.name: hasStreetAddress
relationships.description: indicates a fully-specified address component that consists of a primary address number, predirectional, street name, suffix, postdirectional, and an optional secondary unit

relationships.name: hasStreetName
relationships.description: specifies an identifier for a street in some context (e.g., 'Baker', 'First', 'Main')

relationships.name: hasStreetSuffix
relationships.description: specifies an additional qualifier for a street or other delivery location, such as a dwelling located along a waterway

relationships.name: hasStructureName
relationships.description: specifies an identifier for a building, house, office complex, shopping center, or other structure or group of structures

description._: relates a pooled fund to a sub-fund that is a constituent of the parent fund

relationships.name: hasThirdParty
relationships.description: identifies a party which is not signatory to the party but has some role in the overall context defined by the contract.

description._: specifies a minimum price movement for the security with respect to an exchange
indicates the cash value of one tick, i.e., the minimum price change of the contract

relationships.name: hasTrustee
relationships.description: links a trust to a named trustee

description._: specifies a fee payable by any party that wishes to participate in a contract based on the index after the start of its life

relationships.name: hasValuationTerms
relationships.description: relates a derivative to contractual terms specific to valuation of the underlying asset(s)

relationships.name: hasVestedInIt
relationships.description: indicates the delegated legal authority that is vested in the controlling party

relationships.name: involvesControlledThing
relationships.description: indicates something controlled in the context of a control situation

relationships.name: isAdvisedBy
relationships.description: indicates the party that acts in an advisory capacity to the controlled party

relationships.name: isAffiliateOf
relationships.description: relates a party which directly, or indirectly through one or more intermediaries, controls, or is controlled by, or is under common control by another party to that party

relationships.name: isAssetOf
relationships.description: identifies the owner of an asset

relationships.name: isAuthorizedBy
relationships.description: is endorsed, enabled, empowered, or otherwise permitted by

relationships.name: isAuthorizedThrough
relationships.description: indicates the situation that faciliates endorsement of the authorized party for some purpose

relationships.name: isBasedOnInvestmentEquity
relationships.description: indicates investment-based de facto control, which is is based on the holding of some investment equity by some party

relationships.name: isBeneficialOwnerOf
relationships.description: indicates an asset in which the beneficial owner holds rights (typically voting rights, management rights, etc.) in a beneficial ownership situation

relationships.name: isBeneficiaryOf
relationships.description: specifies the agreement that a beneficiary is named in

relationships.name: isConstitutedBy
relationships.description: the instrument by which an entity is incorporated

relationships.name: isControlledThingIn
relationships.description: indicates the context of control in which something is being controlled

relationships.name: isControllingAffiliateOf
relationships.description: controls directly, or indirectly through one or more intermediaries

relationships.name: isControllingMemberOf
relationships.description: identifies a controlled organization over which the member has some measure of control

relationships.name: isControllingPartyIn
relationships.description: indicates the context of control in which the party plays the role of controlling something

relationships.name: isDirectorOf
relationships.description: indicates the organization that the board member oversees

relationships.name: isEmployedIn
relationships.description: indicates the context of employment in which someone is employed

relationships.name: isEmployeeOf
relationships.description: identifies the formal organization for which the employee works

relationships.name: isEmployingParty
relationships.description: relates a party in the role of employer to the context of employment

relationships.name: isGeneralPartnerOf
relationships.description: indicates the organization that the general partner manages

relationships.name: isGuaranteedBy
relationships.description: relates guaranty to the contract guarantor, i.e., to the legal person providing the guaranty

relationships.name: isGuarantorOf
relationships.description: identifies a party over which a guarantor has some measure of control by virtue of the guarantee

relationships.name: isIncorporatedIn
relationships.description: the legal jurisdiction under which the legal entity is incorporated

relationships.name: isInstrumentOf
relationships.description: relates an instrumentality of some government to the government that it supports

relationships.name: isLegOf
relationships.description: relates a swap leg to the to the swap that includes it

relationships.name: isLimitedPartnerOf
relationships.description: indicates the organization that the limited partner participates in

relationships.name: isLinkedToAccount
relationships.description: connects a given customer account to another customer account

relationships.name: isListedVia
relationships.description: identifies the service responsible for listing the security

relationships.name: isOfficerOf
relationships.description: indicates the organization that the person has some authority over and managerial responsibility for

relationships.name: isOwed
relationships.description: links a creditor to a debt that is outstanding and payable to them

relationships.name: isOwedBy
relationships.description: links a debt to the party that owes it

relationships.name: isOwedTo
relationships.description: links a debt to the party to which it is payable

relationships.name: isOwnedAsset
relationships.description: indicates the context of ownership in which something is an asset

relationships.name: isOwningParty
relationships.description: indicates the context of ownership in which the party plays the role of owner

relationships.name: isParentCompanyOf
relationships.description: indicates a controlled affiliate that it owns at least 50 percent of

relationships.name: isPartyControlling
relationships.description: indicates something controlled that a controlling party has some amount of authority or influence over

relationships.name: isPortfolioCompanyOf
relationships.description: indicates a venture capital firm, a buyout firm, or a holding company that is a financial sponsor (i.e. investor in) of the party

relationships.name: isPremiumOn
relationships.description: an exchange rate expressed as a premium on the spot rate for the currency pair

relationships.name: isPrimaryContractFor
relationships.description: indicates any subordinate agreement, such as a collateral agreement

relationships.name: isPrincipalPartyOf
relationships.description: identifies a legal entity (controlled party) over which a principal has some measure of control

relationships.name: isSeniorTo
relationships.description: indicates that a given share (share class) has higher seniority than the related share, meaning that it gives the holder a higher claim on the assets of the issuer

description._: relates a pooled fund to a parent fund

relationships.name: isSubordinatedTo
relationships.description: indicates the target security (i.e., the one in the range) has a higher priority than the security in question

relationships.name: isSubordinateTo
relationships.description: indicates the primary contract referenced by a subordinate agreement, such as a collateral agreement

relationships.name: isSubsidiaryOf
relationships.description: is controlled directly, or indirectly through one or more intermediaries and owned at least 50 percent by

relationships.name: isSuppliedBy
relationships.description: identifies the party (supplier, vendor, distributor, etc.) that makes a product available

relationships.name: isTriggeredBy
relationships.description: is activated or initiated by

relationships.name: isTrusteeOf
relationships.description: identifies the trust over which a trustee has some measure of control

relationships.name: isUnderwrittenBy
relationships.description: relates an offering to an underwriter involved in raising capital for or distributing the instruments that are the subject of the offering

relationships.name: lists
relationships.description: relates a given exchange-specific security listing to its issue

relationships.name: owes
relationships.description: links a party to a debt that they owe

relationships.name: ownsAsset
relationships.description: identifies an asset that an owner owns

relationships.name: producesRatingsFor
relationships.description: issuer for which ratings are produced or posted through

relationships.name: publishes
relationships.description: prepares and issues material for public consumption

relationships.name: sells
relationships.description: links a party in the role of broker, dealer, vendor, or merchandiser to something that they make available for sale

relationships.name: sellsTo
relationships.description: links a party in the role of broker, dealer, vendor, or merchandiser to a purchaser or potential purchasing party

relationships.name: supersedes
relationships.description: indicates a contract that was executed prior to and is replaced by this contract

relationships.name: supplies
relationships.description: links a party in the role of outfitter, provisioner, distributor, etc. to something that they provide

relationships.name: underwrites
relationships.description: identifies one or more underwriters involved in raising capital for or distributing the instruments that are the subject of the offering

relationships.name: usesRatingParty
relationships.description: rating performer an issuer uses to assess ratings
